Git Hooks are scripts that run automatically before or after Git events. 
Hooks are stored in .git/hooks/. 
Client-side hooks run on the developer's machine. 
Server-side hooks run on the Git server. 
pre-commit is used for checks before committing. 
commit-msg validates commit messages. 
post-commit runs after a successful commit. 
pre-push runs before pushing changes. 
Hooks automate workflows and improve code quality. 
Git Hooks are local and are not shared with the repository by default.

